'After a while they put the blindfold back on and threw the
blanket over my head. Some moments after that I believed I had a
chance to run for it and did,' Bergdahl wrote in his statement.

He was tackled near the outskirts of the village by a large
group of men who pummeled him with their fists and clubbed him
with the butt of an AK-47 rifle, snapping off the stock.

He tried to escape again near the end of his first week as a
prisoner, eluding his captors for about 15 minutes, his statement said, but he was found and beaten
with a thick rubber hose. 

